OL,7,FDelivering his sentencing remarks, the
OL,8,Fjudge added: "Stelmach-Purdie was
OL,9,Fcentral to the commission of these
OL,10,Ffrauds which would not have happened
OL,11,Fwithout his involvement. Without him,
OL,12,Fnone of the other defendants would
OL,13,Fhave become involved in the offences.
OL,15,F"He was responsible for the management
OL,16,Fand control of claims to expenses and
OL,17,Fallowances subject to the supervision
OL,18,Fof his superiors."
